<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2026 01:46:20 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>驼鹿是科罗拉多州本地人还是引进的外来者？新研究表明这些动物已经在该州生活了几个世纪</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/are-moose-colorado-natives-or-introduced-outsiders-new-research-suggests-that-the-animals-have-lived-in-the-state-for-centuries-180989091/</link><description>官员们表示，驼鹿直到 20 世纪 70 年代末才被引入该州。但历史文献和考古证据表明，他们早在那之前就居住在那里</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 20:15:43 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/are-moose-colorado-natives-or-introduced-outsiders-new-research-suggests-that-the-animals-have-lived-in-the-state-for-centuries-180989091/</guid></item><item><title>乡村音乐传奇人物多莉·帕顿的自传音乐剧《探索她从田纳西州东部出发的旅程》将于今年冬天在百老汇上演</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/country-music-legend-dolly-partons-autobiographical-musical-exploring-her-journey-from-east-tennessee-will-hit-broadway-this-winter-180989099/</link><description>《多莉：真正的原创音乐剧》去年在帕顿的家乡纳什维尔首演</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 19:27:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/country-music-legend-dolly-partons-autobiographical-musical-exploring-her-journey-from-east-tennessee-will-hit-broadway-this-winter-180989099/</guid></item><item><title>我们可以通过人为改变气候来缓解超级厄尔尼诺现象吗？一项新研究表明是的</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-we-mitigate-super-el-ninos-by-artificially-changing-the-climate-a-new-study-indicates-yes-180989101/</link><description>研究人员使用计算机模型来观察，如果科学家在过去强烈的厄尔尼诺现象面前使海洋云变亮，会发生什么</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 18:17:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-we-mitigate-super-el-ninos-by-artificially-changing-the-climate-a-new-study-indicates-yes-180989101/</guid></item><item><title>为什么荷兰博物馆的地板上铺满了 800 磅重的奶油花生酱？</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/why-did-this-dutch-museum-cover-the-floor-with-an-800-pound-installation-of-creamy-peanut-butter-180989097/</link><description>“Pindakaasvloer”或“花生酱地板”突显了艺术家 Wim T. Schippers 上个月去世前在其艺术作品中捕捉到的荒谬幽默感</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 18:15:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/why-did-this-dutch-museum-cover-the-floor-with-an-800-pound-installation-of-creamy-peanut-butter-180989097/</guid></item><item><title>科学家刚刚获悉这只蝙蝠在飞行途中吃掉鸟类。文艺复兴时期的画家可能在数百年前就知道了</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-just-learned-that-this-bat-eats-birds-midflight-a-renaissance-painter-may-have-known-about-it-hundreds-of-years-ago-180989096/</link><description>去年秋天，科学家报告了首次已知的大夜蛾在夜间飞行时捕猎和捕食鸣禽的记录。但老扬·勃鲁盖尔 (Jan Brueghel the Elder) 的一幅 17 世纪艺术作品似乎描绘了该物种嘴里叼着带羽毛的猎物飞行</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 16:17:58 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-just-learned-that-this-bat-eats-birds-midflight-a-renaissance-painter-may-have-known-about-it-hundreds-of-years-ago-180989096/</guid></item><item><title>古代DNA表明，哈萨克斯坦铁器时代的“金人”和欧亚大陆的其他精英斯基泰人继承了他们的崇高社会地位</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/kazakhstans-iron-age-golden-man-and-other-elite-scythians-of-eurasia-inherited-their-high-social-status-ancient-dna-suggests-180989089/</link><description>研究人员长期以来一直想知道古代游牧武士的上层成员是否通过个人成就或与生俱来的权利获得了社会地位</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 16:04:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/kazakhstans-iron-age-golden-man-and-other-elite-scythians-of-eurasia-inherited-their-high-social-status-ancient-dna-suggests-180989089/</guid></item><item><title>新研究表明，英国医生用来给患者接种的天花痂可能是将这种致命疾病引入澳大利亚的</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/smallpox-scabs-that-british-doctors-used-to-inoculate-patients-may-have-introduced-the-deadly-disease-to-australia-new-research-suggests-180989093/</link><description>两项新研究发现，18 世纪末乘船抵达的英国殖民者可能引入了天花，对原住民社区的破坏程度远超之前所知</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 14:14:36 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/smallpox-scabs-that-british-doctors-used-to-inoculate-patients-may-have-introduced-the-deadly-disease-to-australia-new-research-suggests-180989093/</guid></item><item><title>新图像显示这颗小行星实际上是两块连体的太空岩石。它们形成一个花生形状的物体，称为“接触二进制”</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-images-reveal-that-this-asteroid-is-actually-two-conjoined-space-rocks-that-form-a-peanut-shaped-object-called-a-contact-binary-180989090/</link><description>日本隼鸟二号航天器飞越该行星时发现了这颗小行星的奇怪形状。探测器收集的数据也将有助于保护地球免受潜在威胁的太空岩石的影响</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2026 21:21:25 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-images-reveal-that-this-asteroid-is-actually-two-conjoined-space-rocks-that-form-a-peanut-shaped-object-called-a-contact-binary-180989090/</guid></item><item><title>波士顿市发现了已知最古老的自由美国黑人墓碑之一，他与马萨诸塞州首府同名</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-city-of-boston-discovered-one-of-the-oldest-known-gravestones-of-a-free-black-american-who-shared-a-name-with-the-massachusetts-capital-180989088/</link><description>他又名塞巴斯蒂安，于 1729 年去世，与塞缪尔·亚当斯、约翰·汉考克和保罗·里维尔合葬。他的一生讲述了美国革命前北方奴隶制与自由的故事</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2026 20:56:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-city-of-boston-discovered-one-of-the-oldest-known-gravestones-of-a-free-black-american-who-shared-a-name-with-the-massachusetts-capital-180989088/</guid></item><item><title>“就像玻璃工厂的爆炸”：弗兰克·盖里曾经装饰摩天大楼大堂的七吨重“冰阵”办公桌即将拍卖</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/like-an-explosion-in-a-glass-factory-frank-gehrys-seven-ton-icehenge-desk-that-once-graced-a-skyscraper-is-up-for-auction-180989087/</link><description>这张桌子是为芝加哥内陆钢铁大厦设计的，由十几块锯齿状的绿色玻璃制成</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2026 18:23:36 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/like-an-explosion-in-a-glass-factory-frank-gehrys-seven-ton-icehenge-desk-that-once-graced-a-skyscraper-is-up-for-auction-180989087/</guid></item><item><title>难道是本王毒害了他的兄弟？一项新的 DNA 分析可能会解开数百年的美第奇家族之谜</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/did-this-duke-poison-his-brother-a-new-dna-analysis-may-solve-the-centuries-old-medici-mystery-180989086/</link><description>研究人员在弗朗切斯科一世·德·美第奇的骨头中发现了疟疾的证据，使他们“以科学的确定性”辩称，导致他于 1587 年死亡的是疾病，而不是砷。</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2026 17:05:02 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/did-this-duke-poison-his-brother-a-new-dna-analysis-may-solve-the-centuries-old-medici-mystery-180989086/</guid></item><item><title>北冰洋可能已经过了一个可能损害食物网并加剧气候变化的关键临界点</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-arctic-ocean-may-have-passed-a-crucial-tipping-point-that-could-harm-food-webs-and-worsen-climate-change-180989083/</link><description>一项新的研究表明，海冰消失似乎引发了硝酸盐营养物的下降，影响了构成海洋食物链基础并吸收大气二氧化碳的微小生物体</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2026 15:36:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-arctic-ocean-may-have-passed-a-crucial-tipping-point-that-could-harm-food-webs-and-worsen-climate-change-180989083/</guid></item><item><title>我们的祖先喜欢贝壳饰品，就像尼安德特人一样。新研究表明这是跨物种共享文化的标志</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/our-ancestors-loved-shell-trinkets-just-like-neanderthals-new-research-suggests-its-a-sign-of-shared-culture-across-species-180989085/</link><description>根据在地中海沿岸石灰岩洞穴中发现的文物，科学家认为这两个物种可能具有相似的生存策略、石器技术和象征传统</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2026 14:26:56 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/our-ancestors-loved-shell-trinkets-just-like-neanderthals-new-research-suggests-its-a-sign-of-shared-culture-across-species-180989085/</guid></item><item><title>生活在东地中海的抹香鲸似乎已经发展出一种与西方不同的方言</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/sperm-whales-living-in-the-eastern-mediterranean-sea-seem-to-have-developed-a-distinct-dialect-from-those-in-the-west-180989084/</link><description>所有地中海抹香鲸都被认为是同一个文化群体的一部分，可以通过独特的滴答声或尾声模式来识别。但录音表明东方生物使用西方鲸鱼尾声的加速版本</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/sperm-whales-living-in-the-eastern-mediterranean-sea-seem-to-have-developed-a-distinct-dialect-from-those-in-the-west-180989084/</guid></item><item><title>澳大利亚海滩上有奇怪的球体被冲上岸。当局称它们可能是“太空球”——火箭中的空燃料容器</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/strange-spheres-washed-ashore-on-an-australian-beach-authorities-say-theyre-probably-space-balls-empty-fuel-vessels-from-a-rocket-180989082/</link><description>这些闪亮的物体——每个物体的大小大约是篮球的两倍——从 7 月 3 日开始出现。当局最初担心它们是危险的，但后来确定它们很可能是安全的太空垃圾。</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 21:15:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/strange-spheres-washed-ashore-on-an-australian-beach-authorities-say-theyre-probably-space-balls-empty-fuel-vessels-from-a-rocket-180989082/</guid></item><item><title>人们认为高大的树木更容易受到干旱的影响。但东南亚的这些高耸植物已经适应了有效地输送水</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/tall-trees-were-thought-to-be-more-vulnerable-to-drought-but-these-towering-plants-in-southeast-asia-have-adapted-to-move-water-efficiently-180989075/</link><description>一项新的研究发现，巨大的龙脑香树具有特殊的适应性，可以将水分输送到最高的树枝，这挑战了它们更容易屈服于干燥条件的假设</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 19:29:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/tall-trees-were-thought-to-be-more-vulnerable-to-drought-but-these-towering-plants-in-southeast-asia-have-adapted-to-move-water-efficiently-180989075/</guid></item><item><title>泰国铁器时代墓地发现一对 2000 年前的金戒指，其中一枚刻有印度文字</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-pair-of-2000-year-old-gold-rings-one-engraved-with-indian-script-was-discovered-in-an-iron-age-burial-ground-in-thailand-180989081/</link><description>该雕刻似乎引用了印度或吠陀占星学中的“吉祥”星座</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 19:19:19 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-pair-of-2000-year-old-gold-rings-one-engraved-with-indian-script-was-discovered-in-an-iron-age-burial-ground-in-thailand-180989081/</guid></item><item><title>这颗巨大的行星可能在其恒星死亡后幸存下来。詹姆斯·韦伯太空望远镜刚刚发现大气层</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-giant-planet-survived-the-death-of-its-star-the-james-webb-space-telescope-just-found-its-atmosphere-180989077/</link><description>对 WD 1856 b（一颗紧密围绕白矮星运行的气态巨行星）的新观测，为太阳在大约 50 亿年后死亡后木星和土星可能发生的情况提供了预览。</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 19:09:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-giant-planet-survived-the-death-of-its-star-the-james-webb-space-telescope-just-found-its-atmosphere-180989077/</guid></item><item><title>你能猜出纸莎草碎片或彩绘陶瓷的起源吗？一名大学生将大都会博物馆的开放访问数据库变成了在线游戏</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/can-you-guess-the-origins-of-papyrus-fragments-or-painted-ceramics-a-college-student-turned-the-mets-open-access-database-into-an-online-game-180989080/</link><description>如果您认为自己是一名艺术史爱好者，请通过 Anthropeum 来测试一下您的聪明才智。该游戏从大都会艺术博物馆的开放获取档案中提取十张图像，并挑战玩家识别每件文物的时间和原产地</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 17:09:01 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/can-you-guess-the-origins-of-papyrus-fragments-or-painted-ceramics-a-college-student-turned-the-mets-open-access-database-into-an-online-game-180989080/</guid></item><item><title>机器人蟑螂可以帮助寻找自然灾害的幸存者。新型潜水服让昆虫能够扩大水下搜索范围</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cyborg-cockroaches-could-help-find-survivors-of-natural-disasters-new-diving-suits-allow-the-insects-to-expand-their-search-underwater-180989066/</link><description>此前，研究人员制造了电子植入物来控制蟑螂的运动，以执行搜救任务。现在，他们制作了可提供氧气的 3D 打印套装，让这些生物能够在水下生存长达三个小时</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 16:01:10 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cyborg-cockroaches-could-help-find-survivors-of-natural-disasters-new-diving-suits-allow-the-insects-to-expand-their-search-underwater-180989066/</guid></item></channel></rss>